     2→/**
     3→ * PaletteFlow Studio – File-system based implementation of the WorkspaceRepository port.
     4→ * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
     5→ * This adapter persists `Workspace` aggregates on disk in a fault–tolerant,
     6→ * versioned, and watchable way.
     7→ *
     8→ *  • Each workspace lives in its own directory under the configured root.
     9→ *  • The actual workspace content is stored in a gzipped JSON document called
    10→ *    `workspace.pfws` (PaletteFlow WorkSpace).
    11→ *  • A lightweight, human-readable `manifest.json` is kept next to it so that
    12→ *    UI code can enumerate workspaces quickly without having to inflate the
    13→ *    full graph.
    14→ *
    15→ * The repository purposefully avoids importing anything from Electron or other
    16→ * front-end frameworks so that it can be reused by CLI tools and background
    17→ * services alike.
    18→ */
